Review saved. Here's the summary:

**1 BUG, 7 QUESTIONs found in `nsqd/protocol_v2.go`:**

| # | Type | Line | Severity | Description |
|---|------|------|----------|-------------|
| 1 | QUESTION | 88 | Low | Unchecked type assertion `err.(protocol.ChildErr)` — panics if future handler returns plain error |
| 2 | QUESTION | 316-321 | Medium | Empty-string topology zone/region matches as equal, silently enabling zone-local priority |
| 3 | QUESTION | 332-334 | Low | Region-local messages counted as zone-local for zone-local clients (inflated stats) |
| 4 | **BUG** | 356 | Low | Off-by-one: `rand.Int31n(100) > sampleRate` delivers sampleRate+1 percent |
| 5 | QUESTION | 867 | Low | MPUB creates topic before body validation (unlike PUB/DPUB) |
| 6 | QUESTION | 619+668 | Low | SUB skips `stateConnected`; that state is dead code for clientV2 |
| 7 | QUESTION | 863 | Medium | MPUB checks auth before reading body — auth failure leaves unread bytes, desynchronizing protocol stream |
| 8 | QUESTION | 297-298 | Low | Non-blocking IdentifyEventChan send could silently drop data (mitigated by startup sync) |

**Assessment: NEEDS DISCUSSION** — Most impactful: Finding 7 (MPUB auth-before-read can corrupt the protocol stream) and Finding 2 (empty-string topology matching changes behavior silently).
